---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="Resources — PerfEco Consulting" description="PerfEco blog: practical articles on organisational performance, executive management and digital transformation in New Caledonia.">
  <Nav />
  <main class="pt-16">

    <section class="bg-navy-dark text-white py-20 px-4">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-teal font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Resources</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">Insights for executives</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-300 text-lg">Practical articles on organisational performance, management and transformation — in the NC &amp; Pacific context.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-20 px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <article class="bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-xl shadow-sm p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <span class="text-xs bg-teal/10 text-teal font-medium px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Strategy</span>
              <span class="text-xs bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 font-semibold px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Series · 2/8</span>
              <time class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 July 2026</time>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mb-3 leading-snug">Strategy alone is not enough: execution as a competitive advantage</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">Harvard Business Review estimates that 40% of strategic value is lost at the execution stage. McKinsey confirms: healthy organisations are 3× more likely to outperform. The 4 pillars of rigorous execution.</p>
            <a href="/en/resources/strategy-alone-is-not-enough" class="text-teal font-semibold text-sm hover:underline inline-flex items-center gap-1">Read the article →</a>
          </article>

          <article class="bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-xl shadow-sm p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <span class="text-xs bg-teal/10 text-teal font-medium px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Execution</span>
              <span class="text-xs bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 font-semibold px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Series · 1/8</span>
              <time class="text-xs text-gray-400">1 July 2026</time>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mb-3 leading-snug">Why strategic plans fail to deliver — even when the strategy is sound</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">A solid strategy is not enough. Execution is the rare and decisive competence. Symptoms, root causes and 4 levers to bridge strategy and concrete results in your organisation.</p>
            <a href="/en/resources/why-strategic-plans-fail" class="text-teal font-semibold text-sm hover:underline inline-flex items-center gap-1">Read the article →</a>
          </article>

          <article class="bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-xl shadow-sm p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <span class="text-xs bg-teal/10 text-teal font-medium px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Governance</span>
              <time class="text-xs text-gray-400">23 June 2026</time>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mb-3 leading-snug">Is a file still standard? The 3 criteria every manager must master</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">A file ceases to be standard as soon as it exceeds the usual framework in complexity, amount or risk. Three simple criteria that prevent costly misclassification.</p>
            <a href="/en/resources/standard-file-escalation-criteria" class="text-teal font-semibold text-sm hover:underline inline-flex items-center gap-1">Read the article →</a>
          </article>

          <article class="bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-xl shadow-sm p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <span class="text-xs bg-teal/10 text-teal font-medium px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Management</span>
              <time class="text-xs text-gray-400">18 June 2026</time>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mb-3 leading-snug">Geopolitical volatility: 5 levers to turn it into a competitive advantage</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">Instability has become structural. How can executive committees transform this constraint into an advantage? A PerfEco reading of McKinsey Quarterly research.</p>
            <a href="/en/resources/geopolitical-volatility-advantage" class="text-teal font-semibold text-sm hover:underline inline-flex items-center gap-1">Read the article →</a>
          </article>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-14 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-8 text-center">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mb-3">Receive future articles</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-6">Analysis and practical guides on executive performance in NC &amp; French Polynesia — no jargon, directly actionable.</p>
          <form name="newsletter-en" method="POST" data-netlify="true" class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 max-w-md mx-auto">
            <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="newsletter-en" />
            <input type="email" name="email" required placeholder="your@email.nc" class="flex-1 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2.5 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-teal" />
            <button type="submit" class="bg-teal hover:bg-teal-dark text-white font-semibold px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm transition-colors">Subscribe</button>
          </form>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
